      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) and relative haemolysis index (RH), which are the regulatory quantities of interest for CPB device clearance. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, residence time) directly inform the power-law hemolysis model inputs. QoI relevance confirmed by regulatory precedent (FDA 2012 guidance on CFD for blood-contacting devices).",
