      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted on the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry as the COU device. Operating conditions span the full COU envelope (2–6 L/min, 2000–4000 RPM). Blood analogue fluid (glycerol-water) used in experiments with viscosity matched to human blood at 37°C. Validation relevance confirmed by geometry identity and operating condition coverage.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
