        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry and span the full COU operating envelope. Fluid properties must be matched to within ±10% of in-vivo conditions. Gradation 2 required at MRL 2."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error is subsumed by the Numerical Code Verification factor (assessed at Gradation 2) and the Discretization Error factor (assessed at Gradation 3). Separate quantification of iterative solver residuals is not required at MRL 2; residuals were confirmed to reach machine-precision levels (< 1e-6) for all simulations, providing adequate assurance without a standalone factor assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is not required at MRL 2 for a Class II device with medium model influence. All simulations were executed by a single qualified analyst following a documented simulation execution plan (SEP-2024-CFD-001) with peer review of boundary condition setup and post-processing scripts. No independent re-execution was required at this risk level."
    },
    {
