      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Reynolds-Averaged Navier-Stokes (RANS) with SST k-omega turbulence closure selected based on published benchmark studies for rotating blood pump flows. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) validated against published red blood cell damage data. Model form uncertainty estimated via comparison against LES results at one operating point; hemolysis index differed by 9%, within the accepted model form uncertainty budget of 15%.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
