        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Model form selection must be justified by published benchmark comparisons for rotating blood pump flows. Model form uncertainty contribution to hemolysis index must be quantified and must not exceed 15% of the predicted value. Gradation 2 required at MRL 2."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "All model inputs (pump geometry from CMM measurements ±0.01 mm, fluid properties from rheometry, rotational speed from encoder data ±0.5 RPM, inlet flow rate from ultrasonic flowmeter ±0.5%) documented with measurement uncertainty. Sensitivity analysis confirmed hemolysis index is most sensitive to inlet flow rate and rotational speed; combined input uncertainty contributes ±7% to hemolysis index prediction.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/model-inputs-ac-001",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "All primary model inputs must be documented with measurement uncertainty. Sensitivity analysis must identify the top three inputs by influence on the primary QoI. Combined input uncertainty must be propagated to the QoI. Gradation 2 required at MRL 2."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Test samples factor is not applicable to CFD-only credibility assessment at MRL 2 where validation is performed against published FDA pump experimental data from a single well-characterised test article. Sample-to-sample variability in pump geometry is addressed through the Model Inputs factor (CMM-measured geometry). No new physical test samples are produced as part of this assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters is scoped out because the validation experiments were conducted on the identical pump geometry used in the COU simulations, with fluid properties matched to within 5% of in-vivo blood properties. No surrogate geometry or scaled test article was used, eliminating the need for a formal equivalency assessment. This scoping decision is consistent with ASME V&V 40 Table 3 guidance for MRL 2 with direct geometry identity."
    }
